### Script Purpose

- Automates the various exports required from a SketchUp `Whitecard` Render File.
- Deals with exporting both image files (png) and CAD Files (dwg)
- Ensures output settings are configured to a standard each time (i.e. image size etc).

---

### Script Helper Functions

`HelperUtils__FetchDate`

- Fetches date for later usage in the naming strings for each file created
- The date will be appended at the end of the file like "__16-Sep-2025"


`HelperUtils__AppendWhitecardNamingToString`

- Applies "__WhitecardImage" into the outputted file names, after the scene name and before the date.
    - Or alternatively if CAD Scene exported applied "__WhitecardCadFile"



### Script Functions

`ExportWhitecard__DetectRequiredScenes`

- Loops through looking for the correct naming prefixes 

- Marks only scenes for export that have correctly named prefixes such as IMG## / IMG### or DWG## / DWG### 

    - Note "#" is placeholder for sequenced numeric integers such as 01 or 003 etc

    

`ExportWhitecard__ExportImageFiles`

- Loops through exporting each IMG marked scene with the following export settings applied.

    ```ImagEexportingConfig
    STANDARD IMAGE EXPORTING CONFIG
    Width                     =    6000 pixels
    Height                    =    4000 pixels
    Aspect Ratio              =    3:2 
    Line scale multiplier	  =    2.00 x
    Anti-alias		  		  =    TRUE
    Transparent background    =    FALSE
    ```

    

`ExportWhitecard__ExportImageFiles`

- Loops through exporting each DWG marked scene with the following export settings applied.

```CadExportingConfig
IMAGE EXPORTING CONFIG

### DWG Configuration

AutoCAD Version  =  Release 12
Full Scale       =  1:1 (Disabled)
In Drawing       =  1 mm
In Model         =  1 mm

### Profile Lines
Export              =  None
Width               =  0 mm
Automatic           =  FALSE
Separate On A Layer =  TRUE

### Section Lines
Export = None
Width = 0 mm
Automatic = FALSE

### Extension Lines
Show Extensions   =    FALSE
Length            =    0 mm
Automatic         =    FALSE

### Miscellaneous
Always Prompt For Hidden Line Options = FALSE
```





```FunctionCallSequence
<STANDARD VALE DESIGN SUITE HEADER>
{write stuff}

MODULE CONSTANTS
----------------

# EXPORT IMAGE CONSTANTS
EXPORT_IMAGE_WIDTH                        =    6000 pixels
EXPORT_IMAGE_HEIGHT                       =    4000 pixels
EXPORT_IMAGE_LINESCALE                    =    2.00 x
EXPORT_IMAGE_ANTIALIAS                    =    TRUE
EXPORT_IMAGE_TRANS_BG                     =    FALSE

# EXPORT CAD CONSTANTS
EXPORT_CAD_VERSION                        =    Release 12
EXPORT_CAD_SCALE                          =    1:1 (Disabled)
EXPORT_CAD_SCALEINDRAWING                 =    1 mm
EXPORT_CAD_SCALEINMODEL                   =    1 mm
EXPORT_CAD_PROFILE_LINES_EXPORT           =    None
EXPORT_CAD_PROFILE_LINES_WIDTH            =    0 mm
EXPORT_CAD_PROFILE_LINES_AUTOMATIC_       =    FALSE
EXPORT_CAD_PROFILE_LINES_SEPARATE_ON_LAYER=    TRUE

# EXPORT CAD SECTION LINES
EXPORT_CAD_SECTION_LINES_EXPORT           =    None
EXPORT_CAD_SECTION_LINES_WIDTH            =    0 mm
EXPORT_CAD_SECTION_LINES_AUTOMATIC        =    FALSE

# EXPORT CAD EXTENSION LINES
EXPORT_CAD_EXTENSION_LINES_SHOW           =    FALSE
EXPORT_CAD_EXTENSION_LINES_LENGTH         =    0 mm
EXPORT_CAD_EXTENSION_LINES_AUTOMATIC      =    FALSE

# EXPORT CAD MISCELLANEOUS
EXPORT_CAD_ALWAYS_PROMPT_HIDDEN_LINES     =    FALSE


HELPER FUNCTIONS
----------------


FUNCTION CALL SEQUENCE 

<USER_TIGGERS_PLUGIN>
  THEN
    ExportWhitecard__DetectRequiredScenes()
  THEN 
    ExportWhitecard__ExportImageFiles()
  THEN 
    ExportWhitecard__ExportCadFiles()
DIALOGUE
  Confirms Files Exported Succesfully or reports failure

```

---

User Interactions

- User launches export via the Vale Design Suite main user interface
  - Updates will need to be made the main UI script and to the Plugin loader script to make this work.
  - Add a new button copying one of the placeholder style buttons already present in the HTML 
- System UI Dialogue asks the target folder to save the outputs


---

### Expected Image File Names

```IMAGE_SCENE_NAMES_AND_EXPECTED_OUTPUT_FILE_NAMING
IMG01__3dView__FrontLeft
	BECOMES
		`IMG01__3dView__FrontLeft__WhitecardImage__16-Sep-2025.png`
		
IMG02__FrontElevation
	BECOMES
		`IMG02__FrontElevation__WhitecardImage__16-Sep-2025.png`
		
IMG03__3dView__TopDown
	BECOMES
		`IMG03__3dView__TopDown__WhitecardImage__16-Sep-2025.png`
```



---

### Expected CAD File Names

- Note the numbers and scene names will be based on what is named within SketchUp

```IMAGE_SCENE_NAMES_AND_EXPECTED_OUTPUT_FILE_NAMING
DWG01__3dView__FrontLeft
	BECOMES
		`DWG01__3dView__FrontLeft__WhitecardCadFile__16-Sep-2025.dwg`
		
DWG02__FrontElevation
	BECOMES
		`DWG02__FrontElevationt__WhitecardCadFile__16-Sep-2025.dwg`
		
DWG03__3dView__TopDown
	BECOMES
		`DWG03__3dView__TopDown__WhitecardCadFile__16-Sep-2025.dwg`
```



